arts.ttl: Tani Oluwaseyi, Wil Trapp lead Minnesota United to 2-1 victory over NYCFC
arts.sum: Minnesota United (4-1-2) — unbeaten in six straight — jumped in front early when Oluwaseyi used assists from Joaquín Pereyra and Kelvin Yeboah in the 2nd minute to score his fifth goal of the season. Tani Oluwaseyi scored for the fifth time this season, Wil Trapp scored for the fifth time in 328 career appearances and Minnesota United beat New York City FC 2-1 at Yankee Stadium on Sunday.
